Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.00,0:35:57.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,并且它们都在单一的变革理论下发挥作用。 \N {\rENG} and that they all function under a single theory of change.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.00,0:35:58.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 极端实用主义，对吗？ \N {\rENG} - Extreme pragmatism  right?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.00,0:35:59.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 是的。 \N {\rENG} - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.00,0:36:02.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你知道，我当初选择 OpenAI 的原因是 \N {\rENG} - You know  the reason I went to OpenAI in the first place
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.00,0:36:03.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道，这是一个非营利组织 \N {\rENG} you know  it was a nonprofit
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.00,0:36:06.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,这是一个我可以去关注安全的地方， \N {\rENG} it was a place where I could go and focus on safety
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.00,0:36:08.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我想随着时间的推移，你知道， \N {\rENG} and I think over time  you know
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.00,0:36:10.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,这可能不太合适 \N {\rENG} that maybe wasn't as good a fit
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.00,0:36:12.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,并且做出了一些艰难的决定。 \N {\rENG} and there were some difficult decisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.00,0:36:13.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我认为，在很多方面， \N {\rENG} And I think  in a lot of ways
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.00,0:36:16.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,在这一点上我真的很信任达里奥和丹妮拉， \N {\rENG} I really trusted Dario and Daniela on that
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.00,0:36:18.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,但我不想离开。 \N {\rENG} but I didn't want to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.00,0:36:21.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,那是我认为我实际上是的东西 \N {\rENG} That was something that I think I was actually
